# AI Trip Planner - Phase 2 (3D UI Overhaul) Complete

I have completely upgraded the frontend to match your request for a **premium 3D UI** and added the missing core pages. 

## What Was Added

### 1. 3D Glassmorphism Design System
- Added `react-parallax-tilt` to introduce depth and perspective to the UI. 
- All major panels (Forms, Itinerary Days, Hotel Cards) now feature a subtle, smooth 3D tilt effect that responds to your mouse movement.
- Added `transform: translateZ` properties to elements inside the glass panels so text and icons visually "pop out" from their backgrounds, creating a true 3D layer effect.
- An animated gradient text effect was added to the main titles.

### 2. New Pages
- **Navbar:** A persistent top navigation bar that blur-filters over the background, allowing easy switching between the Home, Saved Trips, and Auth pages.
- **Login / Register (`/auth`):** A beautifully animated 3D auth card. You can toggle between Login and Register, and the form smoothly expands/collapses using `framer-motion`.
- **Saved Trips (`/saved`):** A dedicated dashboard showcasing past trips in stunning 3D image cards. Currently populated with high-quality mock data (Paris, Japan, New York) to demonstrate the layout.

### 3. Upgraded Existing Pages
- **Home (`/`):** The main search form is now a massive interactive 3D glass panel. 
- **Results (`/results`):** Every day in the generated itinerary, as well as the hotel recommendations, are now individual floating 3D panels that react when hovered over.

## How to Test
The frontend server is still running. Just head over to `http://localhost:5173/` and move your mouse around the cards to feel the 3D perspective! You can navigate between the pages using the new Navbar at the top.

Let me know what you think of the new aesthetics! Next, we could hook up the Login and Saved Trips to the MongoDB backend, or build the AI Chatbot!
